                            <comment id="16923713" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 5 Sep 2019 20:25:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cpettitt-confluent commented on pull request #7302: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8878&quot; title=&quot;Flaky Test AssignedStreamsTasksTest#shouldCloseCleanlyWithSuspendedTaskAndEOS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8878&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8878&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix flaky test AssignedStreamsTasksTest#shouldCloseCleanl&#8230;&lt;br/&gt;
URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7302&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7302&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   &#8230;yWithSuspendedTaskAndEOS&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   The previous approach to testing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8412&quot; title=&quot;Still a nullpointer exception thrown on shutdown while flushing before closing producers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was to look at the logs and&lt;br/&gt;
   determine if an error occurred during close. There was no direct way to&lt;br/&gt;
   detect than an exception occurred because the exception was eaten in&lt;br/&gt;
   `AssignedTasks.close`. In the PR for that ticket (#7207) it was&lt;br/&gt;
   acknowledged that this was a brittle way to test for the exception. We&lt;br/&gt;
   now see occasional failures because an unrelated ERROR level log entry&lt;br/&gt;
   is made while closing the task.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   This change eliminates the brittle log checking by rethrowing any time&lt;br/&gt;
   an exception occurs in close, even when a subsequent unclean close&lt;br/&gt;
   succeeds. This has the potential benefit of uncovering other supressed&lt;br/&gt;
   exceptions down the road.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   I&apos;ve verified that even with us rethrowing on `closeUnclean` that all&lt;br/&gt;
   tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;

